"title": "5572: sword",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5572: sword",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>A hand-wielded blade in common use throughout biblical times as a weapon of war and in OT times as an instrument of execution. The sword is also a symbol of aggression, authority and power.</p>\n<h2>The sword as the principal weapon of war</h2>\n<h3>It was in common use</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod17:13\">EXO 17:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num21:24-Num21:35\">NUM 21:24–21:35</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh11:10-Josh11:12\">JOS 11:10–11:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh19:47\">JOS 19:47</a></p>\n<h3>Swordsmen fought and fell in great numbers</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg3:28-Judg3:30\">JDG 3:28–3:30</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg20:17\">JDG 20:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam24:9\">2SA 24:9</a></p>\n<h3>Some swordsmen showed great strength and ability</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam23:10\">2SA 23:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam21:8-1Sam21:9\">1SA 21:8–21:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam23:12\">2SA 23:12</a></p>\n<h2>The sword used for other purposes</h2>\n<h3>As an instrument of execution and decapitation</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam1:14-2Sam1:16\">2SA 1:14–1:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam15:33\">1SA 15:33</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam17:51\">1SA 17:51</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam22:18-1Sam22:19\">1SA 22:18–22:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs19:1\">1KI 19:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts12:2\">ACT 12:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:35\">ROM 8:35</a></p>\n<h3>For murder</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs19:37\">2KI 19:37</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh6:21\">JOS 6:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs2:34\">1KI 2:34</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts12:2\">ACT 12:2</a></p>\n<h3>For committing suicide</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam31:4-1Sam31:6\">1SA 31:4–31:6</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr10:4\">1CH 10:4</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts16:27\">ACT 16:27</a></p>\n<h2>Metaphorical use of the sword</h2>\n<h3>To symbolise God's opposition to the sinful</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen3:24\">GEN 3:24</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num22:21-Num22:23\">NUM 22:21–22:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num22:31\">NUM 22:31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut33:29\">DEU 33:29</a></p>\n<h3>To symbolise warfare</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev26:6-Lev26:8\">LEV 26:6–26:8</a></p>\n<h3>To symbolise temporal power</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek32:11-Ezek32:12\">EZK 32:11–32:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps45:3\">PSA 45:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic5:6\">MIC 5:6</a></p>\n<h3>To symbolise suffering</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke2:34-Luke2:35\">LUK 2:34–2:35</a></strong></p>\n<h3>To symbolise judgment</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod5:3\">EXO 5:3</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt10:34\">MAT 10:34</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg7:20-Judg7:22\">JDG 7:20–7:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr20:9\">2CH 20:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps7:12\">PSA 7:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa31:8\">ISA 31:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer50:35-Jer50:37\">JER 50:35–50:37</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek11:8-Ezek11:10\">EZK 11:8–11:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek21:3\">EZK 21:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek33:2\">EZK 33:2</a></p>\n<h3>To symbolise the word of God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph6:17\">EPH 6:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb4:12\">HEB 4:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev1:16\">REV 1:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev2:12\">REV 2:12</a></p>",
